**Netflix Data Analysis Project**
**Overview**
This project focuses on analyzing Netflix Movies and TV Shows using Python and Power BI.
The main objective is to explore the dataset, clean the data, identify trends, and create visualizations for better understanding of Netflix content.
________________________________________
**Technologies Used**
•	Python
•	Pandas
•	NumPy
•	Matplotlib
•	Seaborn
•	Jupyter Notebook
•	Power BI
________________________________________
**Dataset Information**
The dataset contains details about Netflix content such as:
•	Title
•	Type (Movie/TV Show)
•	Director
•	Country
•	Release Year
•	Rating
•	Genre
•	Duration
________________________________________
**Project Workflow**

**1. Data Cleaning**
•	Removed unnecessary columns
•	Handled missing values
•	Checked duplicate records

**2. Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)**
•	Analyzed Movies vs TV Shows
•	Checked content growth over years
•	Identified top countries
•	Explored ratings and genres

**3. Data Visualization**
Created visualizations using:
•	Count Plots
•	Bar Charts
•	Histograms
•	Heatmaps

**4. Power BI Dashboard**
Built an interactive dashboard to visualize:
•	Content distribution
•	Ratings analysis
•	Country-wise content
•	Genre analysis
•	Year-wise trends
________________________________________
**Key Insights**

•	Netflix contains more Movies than TV Shows
•	Content growth increased rapidly after 2015
•	USA has the highest number of Netflix titles
•	Drama and International genres are the most popular
•	TV-MA and TV-14 are the most common ratings
